x \delta \theta = - \frac{\delta x \tan(\theta)}{\sec^2{\theta}} = - \sin(\theta) \cos(\theta) \delta x
\delta r = \frac{\delta x}{\cos(\theta)} + \frac{\sin(\theta)}{\cos^2(\theta)} (-\sin(\theta) \cos(\theta) \delta x) = \frac{1-\sin^2(\theta)}{\cos(\theta)} \delta x = \cos(\theta) \delta x
\frac{\partial r}{\partial x} = \cos(\theta) = \frac{x}{\sqrt{x^2+y^2}}
